
There is a major issue in that tasks that have time spent on them are being shown as "never done" or the like, only because they haven't been marked as done. I'm looking for some way to balance between the app seeing that those tasks have been done to a reasonable degree. Like I want to say even just one section of time over a minute should mark it as having been done, but for something like a 2 hour task, this seems overly generous. I'm not sure how to approach this really. I'm thinking that on first opening of the site or app on each day, the app should scan the previous days tasks. Any task done that met its minimum time requirement should be marked as done. Any task done that didn't meet its minimum should be included in a dialog that the app opens, showing the time spent relative to expected, and whether that task should be marked as "having been done". One possible bug that could interrupt this flow is if the user doesn't visit for a day and so the day before that never gets checked. So we need to handle for that eventuality by storing the "last day visited" or something of that nature. Do you see any issues with this approach or have any recommendations for a different approach?

Any Scheduled dates for tasks should be cleared if the current date is past the scheduled date